FBIS4-65364 "drweu095_k_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-095 Daily Report 12 May 1994 PORTUGAL Government, President To Appoint Military Chiefs Government, President To Appoint Military Chiefs LD1205205594 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television in Portuguese 1800 GMT 12 May 94 LD1205205594 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television Portuguese BFN [Excerpt] Military chiefs will be appointed exclusively by politicians. The Council of Ministers today approved a bill, to be submitted to parliament, giving the government and the president of the Republic the power to appoint military chiefs. Lists of names chosen by the top brass of the three branches of the Armed Forces will disappear. The Ministry of Defense will make its choices and the president will sign the nominations. [passage omitted]
